<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103593946748199></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103593946748199><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103593946748199>RE: new chanter</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103593946748199#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>172 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 29th 8:17 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.45]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>In the early levels you will get way more bang for your buck if you outfit your character with HP/Mana gear rather than STA/INT gear.&nbsp;&nbsp;The bonus to mana for extra intelligence at early levels is very small, but if you just get straight mana gear, the bonus is sizeable and noticeable.  Same thing goes with hitpoints.<br><br>Some middish level items come to mind.<br><br>Orc Fang Earrings I think have 15HP on them each.<br>Frozen Mantle has 10 mana.<br>HP/Mana rings and bracers can be made by jewelers.<br>Robe of the Oracle has 25 mana.<br>Chipped Bone Collar has 10Mana and 10HP.<br>Cloak of the Ry'Gorr Oracles has 10Mana.<br>Imp Skin Gloves have 10 mana.<br>Golden Jaded Bracelet 15 mana and 15HP.<br><br>Those are the items that I can think of, I'm sure there's tons more out there.  Do a search on this site to find more.<br><br>Of course as you level up you will want to start thinking more about INT, CHA, and STA (in that order, IMO), but like I said before, Mana and HP will get you way further in early levels.<br><br>Have fun,<br><br>-Yizz<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
