<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103535187697909></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103535187697909><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103535187697909>RE: Research</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103535187697909#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>172 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 23rd 2:03 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>About 30 of the Enchanter spells from level 16 to 50 can only be obtained through research.&nbsp;&nbsp;That is, you can't buy them from vendors.  They must be researched by the players.<br><br>In order to research spells you'll need to buy a Tome of Endless Enchantments first.  I got mine at the caster guild in West Freeport, from one of the merchants outside that stand around the little pool out there.  I think it was the bird guy but I don't remember for sure.  I'm sure if you nose around most of the enchanter guilds you can find one.<br><br>Once you have the Tome, you place two sequential pages (e.g. Velishouls Tome Page 8 and Velishouls Tome Page 9) inside the Tome (it's a container like a backpack) and then push the Combine button.  You'll find that sometimes the pages are ripped in half, in which case you put the right and left half (e.g. Tasarins Grimoire Page 23 Left and Right) in the Tome and press Combine.  Lastly, you'll also come across Faded Pages (e.g. A Faded Velishouls Tome Page) which you will put in the Tome alone and press Combine in order to unfade it.  Once unfaded, you'll know what page it is and be able to combine it with its match.<br><br>Research is just like any other skill in EQ, it must be practiced in order to become proficient at it.  If you really want to pursue it, I suggest putting quite a few practice points into it to save yourself some time and hassle.  <br><br>Collecting the pages to research is not a very fun task either.  They drop off MOBs all over Norrath, so grab them when you can.  Also, get into the habit of checking vendors whenever you are buying or selling.  Other players frequently sell the pages to vendors and you can buy them usually from 1p to 5p or more.  <br><br>At level 48, I had two backpacks full of pages without the other halves that I needed.  So it takes a lot of space.  I finally just bought all the rest of my research spells and sold all the pages to vendors.  What a relief!  And, of course, even when you do find a matching pair, you still must have sufficient skill in order to successfully combine them into the spell.<br><br>Sounds fun, right?  Well, the good news is that you don't have to research your own spells, even less so now that SoL is around.  You can buy all of your spells from other players up in the Bazaar on the moon, and usually the prices are fairly reasonable.<br><br>Unless you thrive on extremely challenging undertakings, this is my recommendation.  Let someone else do the work and fork over the plat for their sweat.<br><br>Lastly, there is an alternative to practicing and raising your skill on the actual pages, which is the research quests.  To do this, you'll need to get a greater lightstone (drops off of willowisps) and take it to Mrysila in WK at the Gypsy Camp or to Smith Tv'ysa in SRo.  Before approaching either one, make sure you are not KOS, and if you are use your enchanter spells to get non-KOS.  When you give either one the GLS they will give you a Concordance of Research.<br><br>With the Concordance you can run all over gathering supplies to combine in order to practice.<br><br>That's a good, brief introduction.  I suggest that you visit <a href="http://eq.crgaming.com" target=_new>http://eq.crgaming.com</a> and go to the Enchanter area and then to the research area.  This site has a very comprehensive list of the research spells, components, and the practice quests.  That's where I got all of my info from as well.<br><br>Good luck.<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
