<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103427679494707></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103427679494707><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103427679494707>RE: HUH</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103427679494707#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2440><span id=Scholar>Dargadin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>370 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 10th 3:24 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.16]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Mezmerize makes the MoB stop and go non-agro for a while, temporarially taking them out of the fight.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>There is also the AoE version (Mezmerization) which can stop all the MoBs except the one your main tank is attacking, but the AoE version only lasts 24 seconds.  Commonly, the Enchanter uses AoE Mez, then follow up with a longer-lasting, single-target mez on each MoB.<br><br>Mez will break if aonyone attacks or casts a damage spell on the mezzed mob, but non-damaging debuffs like Slow, AC/STR reduction, Mind Wipe, and others will NOT break Mez.<br>&nbsp;<br>______________________________________<br><b>Dargadin, Barbarian Shaman of the 53rd Season</b><br>Darg&nbsp;&nbsp; 41 Barb Warrior<br>Cyrius 21 Eru Wizard<br><b><span style='color: blue;'>Legions of Ragnorak</span style='color: blue;'><br>Ayonae Ro Server</b></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
