	   <tr><td colspan=2>I play a human enchantress who worships Karana.&nbsp;&nbsp;Does that tell you I had no clue what I was doing when I created my character?  I have a hideously low INT even for a human because... I was clueless at the time.  I took up jewelry making at level 8 so I have *never* had any money to buy gear as I wasted sooo much cash (from failures I would not have had if my INT had been higher).<br><br>So... if I can do it, most of you can too.<br><br>There is a single spectre spawn outside the tunnel to Fear.  Make a pet, cast your best bezerker STR series spell on him just before battle.<br><br>1) Root and pray to Karana<br>2) Tash<br>3) DoT<br>4) Nuke<br><br>As soon as root breaks (which may be as son as you cast your DoT) be prepared to cast Fear.  Spectres run so slowly they are as good as snared and your pet will beat him up.  ReDoT and Nuke as needed, but you may need to not nuke when you first start out.<br><br>Loot up.<br><br>The great thing is that if you ran the Stein of Moggok Quest when you first could only about 10 times you have decent faction with the ogre vendors outside Oggok with your illusion (if you even need that ... because of the religion thing, I did).  I made about 22K and got these 7 levels soloing in less than 2 weeks (and got some nice gems which I immediantly turned into jewelry!! Sorry... habit).  Between battles you might get attacked while meditating, but by the time you notice the mobs will be dead.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
