	   <tr><td colspan=2>Calanctus pretty much hit it, but I'm bored ....<br><br>ERUDITE:&nbsp;&nbsp;Highest INT, 3rd highest CHA, poor in all other stats.  No night vision.  Neutral faction.<br><br>HIGH ELF:  4th high INT (still good), highest CHA, lowest STR/STA.  Some night vision.  Good faction.<br><br>HUMAN:  Lowest (by far) INT, 2nd highest CHA, good STR/STA.  No night vision.  Neutral faction.<br><br>GNOME:  Third highest (still good) INT, @#%^ty CHA, bad STR, ok STA.  Some night vision.  Neutral faction.<br><br>DARK ELF:  2nd highest INT, @#%^ty CHA, bad STR/STA.  Excellent night vision.  Hide ability (a pretty cool feature, especially at earlier levels.)<br><br><br>As a note, neutral faction (in my opinion for an enchanter) is a GOOD thing.<br><br>High Elf is a good choice if you want to be a goodie-goodie, Dark Elf is good if you want to be bad.  Erudite or Human are both excellent for being neutral.  Gnome is good if you want to be a gnome.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
