<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103086432446068></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103086432446068><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103086432446068>RE: Race</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103086432446068#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=167783><span id=Scholar>Calanctus</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>28 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Sep 1st 3:25 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Which Race would make the best Enchanter? That depends on what angle you are working from.&nbsp;&nbsp;For instance...<br><br>If you have a lot of extra twink gear because you have a level 60 main already, then:<br>It does not matter, your gear will shore up your weaknesses<br><br>If you hate casting night vision spells over and over again:<br>Pick High Elf or Dark Elf<br><br>If you don't have any gear, and want the highest possible starting mana (and therefore the highest possible starting intelligence):<br>Pick Erudite<br><br>If you want the highest starting Charisma so you don't need to bother too much with it later so you can concentrate on resists:<br>Pick High Elf<br><br>If you want to work Tradeskills and Tinker:<br>Pick Gnome<br><br>If you want &quot;hide&quot; ability:<br>Pick Dark Elf<br><br>As you can see there is no clear cut &quot;best&quot; class.  It all depends on how you want to start.  Gear tends to shore up any initial weaknesses and eventually all chanters are about the same in terms of stats and resists.<br><br>Even though I play a High Elf, In retrospect, I would pick a class that had one or more of the following:  nightvision, hide, or tinker<br><br>Please note these are just my opinions and you are free to agree or disagree as you see fit.<br><br>Best Regards,<br><br>Calanctus of Sol Ro<br>lvl 60 Phantasmist<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
