	   <tr><td colspan=2>Update time:&nbsp;&nbsp;Okay, it was update time a while ago, but i forgot about posting the followup.<br><br>As a few of you mentioned, getting the stein was not a problem, though strolling through Oggok gave me the screaming heebie-jeebies. ;-)<br><br>Actually, the most danger i found myself in was on the Isle of Erollisi.  After purchasing my Kiola nut, i stepped outside and prepared to gate out.  Suddenly, i found myself getting attacked by some ornery half-elf!  Unfortunately, I had never summoned an animation upon setting foot on the island, so i was getting well and truly smacked upon.  Luckily, i -did- have root memorized, so i rooted the bugger, backed off, and gated.  (I had not gone there with the intent of fighting, and did not want to have to go back.)<br><br>In Oggok, i was surprised to find that my spells caused ogres to be amiable or even kindly towards me.  All things considered, Oggok was one of the easiest parts of this quest, much to my surprise.<br><br>So, thank you very much one and all for your advice and feedback.  (Lifts his glass)  Cheers!<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>40th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
