<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103042283716428></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103042283716428><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103042283716428>RE: Where to go?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103042283716428#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>172 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 27th 12:46 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.45]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would recommend you check out OT with one major caveat.&nbsp;&nbsp;Get into or form yourself a 'tower' group.  There is a one-room building (if you want to even call it a building ... more like a ruin I guess) where three (if memory serves ... if not three than four) Sarnaks spawn.  They are static spawns so as long as the room isn't camped, they will be there waiting.<br><br>Breaking the room is not too tough.  Have somebody pull them outside the building where the group is waiting and mezz the two while they kill the first.  Once you have the spawn broken, move into the building and set up camp.  There are many wandering MOBs in the area that you can pull into the tower.  With the additional three spawns inside you can keep pretty busy.<br><br>Some more advantages:<br><br>-no competition for pulls - if the tower is camped, I have NEVER seen another group even remotely nearby.<br>-no 'goons - they don't wander way out to these parts, which is nice for the 'goodies'.  Of course enchanters should never have to worry about the 'goons no matter what, but it's a good selling point to others.<br>-excitement - as far as outdoor zones go, this was one of my favorite camp spots ever.<br><br><br>Getting there:<br><br>The tower is very close to the zone line to Warsliks Woods.  Follow the South zone wall East all the way to the SE corner then turn North and keep following the East zone wall.  You will see it on your left side.<br><br><br>The downside:<br><br>-It is hard to initially convince people to go there, because they are mostly mindless followers of the status quo.  =)  Once I convinced some people, though, I had a lot of new friends that were more than willing to join me over there whenever I was in the zone.<br><br><br>Give it a shot.  If you don't like it, go somewhere else.  I never liked DL much myself.  I got 44 there and then soloed HGs in Rathe.  That was fun if you like soloing.<br><br>Good luck, and ...<br><br>Have fun.<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
