<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102947412649324></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102947412649324><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=102947412649324>RE: Pages for Research</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=102947412649324#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=167783><span id=Scholar>Calanctus</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>28 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 16th 1:13 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hiyas again,<br><br>Generally, research materials drop off of mobs that are the same level as the spell you need to research. If you need to find research for a 20th level spell, then you will have to find a zone where there are level 20 mobs to kill.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you already know this, please disregard.<br><br>Regarding the runes that drop off of the crocs in Oasis, there are two types.   There are normal research runes and there are also special runes for a wizard quest.  This may be why you see a lot of runes dropping.<br><br>When I was a level 16 enchanter, I hunted in Oasis.  In the 20-30 range, i was at High Keep and South Karana.  Splitpaw was nice mid 20's+. After that I off to Cazic Thule (before the &quot;Enhancement&quot;) to cut my teeth on &quot;real&quot; crowd control.  You can find the same mobs out in feerrott nowadays.  After 35, I went to Lower Guk til my mid 40's or so.  This may be considered &quot;old school&quot; now with the plethora of new zones, but I still think they are good spots.  The mobs on average have less hps than on kunark, velious or luclin, so you will be able to kill more, level faster and have a better chance of aquiring the research material you need.  On the downside, loot will generally not be as good or unique.<br><br>Hope that helps some.<br><br>Best regards,<br><br>Calanctus of Sol Ro<br>lvl 60 Phantasmist<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
